
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to add nodes to the current node's children. It retrieves nodes using the [get-nodes] slot from the [.arguments] node, specifically the [limit] and [offset] nodes, and adds them as children to the node where the [add] slot is invoked. The [add] slot is used to dynamically modify the node structure by appending specified nodes to a target node.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
